.SH NAME
AudioListener \- AudioListener
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]AudioListener\f[R] interface represents the position and
orientation of the unique person listening to the audio scene, and is
used in audio spatialization.
All \f[CR]PannerNode\f[R]s spatialize in relation to the
\f[CR]AudioListener\f[R] stored in the
\f[CR]BaseAudioContext.listener\f[R] attribute.
.PP
It is important to note that there is only one listener per context and
that it isn\[cq]t an \f[CR]AudioNode\f[R].
